      h2 An Interesting Bug
      ul
        li In 2018, Docker and Razer Synapse 
          a(href="https://twitter.com/foone/status/1229641258370355200") could not run together
        li Each program intended to limit to one running copy of 
          strong itself
        li They both did something like this:
      pre
        code
          | string.Format("Global\{0}", (object) Assembly.↵
          |     GetExecutingAssembly().GetType().GUID);
      strong Can you spot the bug?

    section.slide
      h2 An Interesting Bug
      pre
        code
          | string.Format("Global\{0}", (object) Assembly.↵
          |     GetExecutingAssembly().GetType().GUID);
      br
      p 
        span.code .GetType()
        |  returns .NET's 
        span.code System.Reflection.RuntimeAssembly
      ul
        li So each app was sharing 
          strong .NET's GUID
        li Apparently this was from a flawed 
          a(href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/502303/how-do-i-programmatically-get-the-guid-of-an-application-in-net2-0/502323#502323") StackOverflow answer
        li Beware the uncritical copy/paste!


